        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Congregation Shearith Israel&#44;<lb/>
                קק שארית ישראל<lb/></p>
            <p>New York&#44; Oct 27&#91;&#44;&#93; 5646<lb/>
                1885<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Rev S Morais<lb/>
                Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Having so far troubled<lb/> you with the correspondence with Mr<lb/> Massiah&#44; we take the liberty of Enclosing<lb/> our letter to him&#44; and asking you to forward<lb/> it&#44; as it is&#44; or translated into Italian<lb/> with such Explanations as you may<lb/> deem requisite&#45;&#45; You know the Rev<lb/> Mr Mendes is our Minister&#44; and by our<lb/> Constitution also Hazan&#44; and therefore<lb/> the official designation of Mr Massiah<lb/> will be that of Assistant Hazan&#58;<lb/> but should Mr Massiah prove&#44; as we<lb/> hope&#44; in ability and character what<lb/> we are looking for&#44; his duties  will be<lb/> virtually all or nearly those&#44; pertain&#45;<lb/>ing to a Hazan&#45;&#45; The term of the<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>present incumbent Expires on the  15&#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/> of next August&#44; but still we  would<lb/> like to have Mr Massiah come over<lb/> as soon as possible&#44; so that we may<lb/> know in ample time&#44; as to his fitness<lb/> &#38;c&#45;&#45; To be sure the fact that he<lb/> does not speak English is somewhat<lb/> unfortunate&#44; but no doubt he would<lb/> soon master that sufficiently to get<lb/> along&#8212;The Salary will not be<lb/> less than &#36;2500 per annum&#45;&#45;<lb/> Mr M can come by Steamer from <lb/> Marseilles or Havre&#8212;we can send<lb/> him the tickets both ways&#44; if such<lb/> is desired&#44; probably at lower rates<lb/> than he could get them&#8212;Again<lb/> apologising for the trouble we have<lb/> put you to&#44; and thanking your for your<lb/> great Kindness in this Matter &#38;c<lb/> we remain&#44; Sincerely and gratefully<lb/></p>
            <p>Joseph Blumenthal<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>T&#91;...&#93;David<lb/>
                David M. Piza<lb/>
                Committee Board of<lb/> Trustees<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Please address any  answer<lb/> as to<lb/>
                Joseph Blumenthal<lb/>
                31 Chambers St<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
